                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6412.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-27T13:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Zapata, Salazar, Argumedo and all rebel chiefs in Vera Cruz and Nuevo Laredo
                    have submitted to the Provisional Government. Orozco has announced his
                    adherence. Difficulties still exist in the States of Coahuila, Sonora, Chihuahua
                    and Durango.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
